### Observed behavior

I have a work queue scenario where a worker is fetching messages one by one to process them.

The time it takes to process a message is variable and some messages can take a long time to process.
An inactive threshold is set on the consumer to have the NATS server automatically clean up the consumer.

I originally opened an issue for the consumer getting removed while actively processing a message:  https://github.com/nats-io/nats.go/issues/1900. This was fixed by https://github.com/nats-io/nats-server/pull/7052

To ensure messages are redelivered quickly when processing fails, the `AckWait` is deliberately configured lower than the max processing time. `InProgress` is called to extend the processing window while a message is getting worked on.

The consumer is getting detected as inactive and gets removed while working on a message.

### Expected behavior

Pending acks are now counted toward consumer activity, I'd expect sending an `InProgress` acknowledgment to similarly count and prevent the consumer's removal.

### Server and client version

Server: Build of `26797a84c2c691176511ea3b3b0e9e841c64fed8`
Client: github.com/nats-io/nats.go v1.43.0

### Host environment

_No response_

### Steps to reproduce

Go script to reproduce:

```go
package main

import (
	"context"
	"log"
	"os"
	"os/signal"
	"syscall"
	"time"

	"github.com/nats-io/nats.go"
	"github.com/nats-io/nats.go/jetstream"
)

func main() {
	url := os.Getenv("NATS_URL")
	if url == "" {
		url = nats.DefaultURL
	}

	nc, err := nats.Connect(url)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}
	defer nc.Drain()

	js, err := jetstream.New(nc)
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	ctx, cancel := signal.NotifyContext(context.Background(), os.Interrupt, syscall.SIGTERM)
	defer cancel()

	stream, err := js.CreateStream(ctx, jetstream.StreamConfig{
		Name:      "queue1",
		Subjects:  []string{"queue1.>"},
		Retention: jetstream.WorkQueuePolicy,
	})
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	consumer, err := stream.CreateOrUpdateConsumer(ctx, jetstream.ConsumerConfig{
		Name:              "queue1-consumer",
		FilterSubject:     "queue1.>",
		InactiveThreshold: time.Second * 5,
		AckWait:           time.Second * 10,
	})
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	sub, err := consumer.Consume(func(msg jetstream.Msg) {
		ctx, cancel := context.WithCancel(ctx)
		defer cancel()

		meta, err := msg.Metadata()
		if err != nil {
			log.Printf("Error getting metadata: %v", err)
			return
		}
		log.Printf("Received message %d, delivered %d\n", meta.Sequence.Stream, meta.NumDelivered)

		go func() {
			interval := consumer.CachedInfo().Config.AckWait * 70 / 100
			ticker := time.NewTicker(interval)
			defer ticker.Stop()

			for {
				select {
				case <-ctx.Done():
					return
				case <-ticker.C:
					log.Printf("Extending ack wait for message %d\n", meta.Sequence.Stream)
					if err := msg.InProgress(); err != nil {
						log.Printf("Error in calling in progress: %v", err)
					}
				}
			}
		}()

		time.Sleep(time.Second * 20)

		msg.Ack()
		log.Printf("Acked message %d\n", meta.Sequence.Stream)
	}, jetstream.ConsumeErrHandler(func(consumeCtx jetstream.ConsumeContext, err error) {
		log.Printf("Error consuming message: %v", err)
	}), jetstream.PullMaxMessages(1))
	if err != nil {
		log.Fatal(err)
	}

	<-ctx.Done()

	sub.Stop()
	<-sub.Closed()
}
